CASTING CALL - ASAP

13/02/25

The Party No One Wanted (Short Film)

**A dark comedy about grief and family relationships.**

Robbie and Mary have to get through an excruciating memorial that has a DJ, karaoke and a pregnancy announcement / gender reveal planned by their half sister Lisa.

Please fill in this form if interested: [https://forms.gle/4N4tdaMwFQ6aBnga7](https://forms.gle/4N4tdaMwFQ6aBnga7) 

* **Shooting 6th - 9th March in TW19**
* Auditions in Elephant and Castle within the next few weeks
* **Travel Expenses Paid**
* There are also multiple smaller roles and extras needed please see the form for more information
* Student film hoping to go to Film festivals
* **Steve** (57-70yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Mary, Robbie and Lisa‚Äôs dad doesn‚Äôt get involved in the arguing he‚Äôs still devastated by the loss of his wife but insists he‚Äôs fine.
* **Lisa** (39-47yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Self centred and definitely doesn‚Äôt know whats appropriate at a memorial. 
* **Natalie** (49-65yrs)
   * A close family friend who has taken on a bit of a motherly role to everyone, kind and soft spoken.
* **Bill** (50-65yrs) 
   * The drunk best friend of steve who has awful timing for his awkward comments. Very funny character

**Character Bios: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing)** **

**Director‚Äôs Statement: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing)

**CREW NEEDED: SAG-AFTRA SHORT FILM (PAID): LOS ANGELES**

Hi everyone: we‚Äôre still staffing up for **"Dead or Alive,"** a 7-minute SAG-AFTRA short film (Micro-Budget) shooting on location in **Agua Dulce, CA**.

This is a gritty, performance-driven Western drama centered on the tension between a disgraced lawman and his outlaw brother. We are looking for crew members who enjoy focused sets, strong visuals, and festival-bound work.

Project Details:
* **Genre:** Western / Drama
* **Shoot Dates:** February 21st & 22nd, 2026
* **Location:** Agua Dulce, CA (Exterior/Interior)
* **IMDB:**[[[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39387683](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39387683)](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39387683?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExQ0I3RDI2dDc1MXFyRWRsVHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR4TIcJv0C2YYHHo-ERGoOcd8Urxciv0tuIhlSc0Jobj0ETVSjbowf9pOkNUKQ_aem_6r-M0lG6GSpo3kM2R2lpGw)](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt39387683%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExQ0I3RDI2dDc1MXFyRWRsVHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR6HE8cb2bt-v1KroSlDYm6MyS0bsJRK8HC_CO_MH2aPt3AU8OLC3t9RCl1iwQ_aem_QI0ob-rJfoMJLSPfJnjj0g&h=AT1CJeksz293B148HhgpyTdWHBWkNxemz0BA2loW5dFf47y-lQN63b1m1boEBgd-LDzo_TZ-9DXQ2HgnzFc3BNdD_FokGsISwrWXXy33ZdMXPFu5K-trMxRQ2ps8KdaA1dwXl24AlA&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT0Ww4d--6-bNBkn89-G9q9w6ESCKCsXkJtXInFGe943OZhfu8gfpJwT1U39g8qy-B3tlHbpc-jCClmBWnKnWi-zznTq8mfJ_NXz0Gohe77NfF6xBQDcGbtWGF4NOctBeOzgvn5vCP1-VMMNS-_DFnLUV-tuGNRIQk-9tHESUOaE76G3HnCsBpd9UX16UBxglY7L7yKD2X4Mf7pLSk-55vMSPIZw5Q)
* Pay: Modest but paid. Meals, credit and footage provided. 
## 

Positions Still Hiring: üìÑ
* **Sound Mixer** (With kit preferred) 
* **Grips **
## 
Positions Hiring Completed: ‚úÖ
* **Wardrobe / Costume Designer** (Period-appropriate Western wear) ‚úÖ
* **Hair & Makeup Artist** (Naturalistic/Gritty looks) ‚úÖ
* **Production Coordinator ‚úÖ**
* **Production Assistants ‚úÖ**

To Apply: Please **DM me** with the following information and so I can make sure to find your message in my requests:
1. Your role
2. Confirmation of availability for Feb 21 and 22
3. Your day rate
4. Link to your IMDB, reel, portfolio, or website
etc

Thanks in advance!

**Spencer**
Producer: *Dead or Alive*

items.text:
CASTING CALL: THE COLLECTOR (Short Film)

Production: Independent Short Film

Genre: Supernatural Horror / Psychological Thriller

Location: York, England

Shoot Dates: April 12th and 13th

Compensation: Unpaid. Catering provided. This project is intended as the beginning of an ongoing creative collaboration.

Synopsis:

The Collector explores the predatory nature of darkness and the dangerous misunderstanding of vulnerability. Innocence is not seen as purity, but as something to be consumed.

Roles Available:

Grace (Female, 40s) Lead

A composed, intelligent professional with a quiet but formidable presence. Calm, controlled, and shaped by survival.

Emma (Female, 14‚Äì15) Lead

Curious and isolated. Emotionally intuitive and observant. Becomes the focus of the Entity‚Äôs attention.

The Entity (Female) Supporting

A physical, unsettling presence of pale flesh and darkness. Strong physical performance required. Heavy makeup FX and sclera lenses involved.

David (Male, late 30s to 40s) Supporting

Emma‚Äôs father. Practical and protective, pushed into a terrifying supernatural confrontation.

Father Benedict (Male, 60s) Supporting

A frail but determined priest attempting an exorcism. Spiritually authoritative despite physical weakness.

Submission Requirements:

Please click on the Google forms link below to submit your answers: https://forms.gle/sbUWJAjRM8iJmJFMA

DROPS ‚Äì Making waves through the arts is casting performers aged 18+ for Bloomin‚Äô Church!, a heartfelt new play heading to the Edinburgh Festival Fringe in summer 2026, followed by a South West tour in October 2026.

items.text:
F√ºr unseren Kurzfilm ‚Äû7 Floors to Midnight‚Äú suchen wir einen mutigen Hauptdarsteller.

 Idealerweise bist Du √ºber 40. Herausforderung: Du spielst g√§nzlich unbekleidet. Wichtig w√§re mir, dass Du authentisch spielst. Text ist √ºberschaubar, Emotionen sind wichtig.

Es handelt sich um einen hochwertig produzierten Kurzfilm, der international auf div. Festivals eingereicht wird. Das Ziel ist, min. einen Filmpreis zu schnappen ;-)

Du spielst Claus, den Loser. Insgesamt wirkst Du ziemlich verwahrlost, lebst in einer kleinen, r√§udigen Wohnung und bist mit Deine Leben unzufrieden - bis pl√∂tzlich eine nackte Sch√∂nheit an Deine T√ºr klopft. Mutig weil: Es wird eine (angedeutete) Liebesszene mit Kuss geben.

Es ist lediglich ein kleines, professionelles Team beim Dreh anwesend (Closed Set)

Drehort ist in G√∂ttingen in der Nacht vom 28.2. auf den 1.3.

Hotelkosten, Anfahrt (ICE), ggf. Taxitransfer vom Bahnhof, Catering etc. werden selbstverst√§ndlich √ºbernommen. Zudem zahle ich f√ºr diese nicht ganz allt√§gliche Rolle 300,- Euro an Gage.

Bewerbungen bitte mit Bild, Vita und Telefonnummer an sebastian@fesser.tv (bitte KEINE PNs, die gehen hier immer unter!). Stichwort: Claus

üé• **CASTING CALL ‚Äì Actor/Actress for a Training Video**

Hi there! üëã

At Panda Motion, we are looking for an actor or actress to play the role of a host/narrator in an approx. 25-minute cybersecurity training video series.

**Details:**

üé¨ Project: Corporate training video (6-7 episodes, approx. 4 minutes each, 25 mins total) for an LMS platform

üìç Location: Krak√≥w or surrounding area

üìÜ Date: 1 shooting day (late February / early March - TBD)

üì≤ Usage Rights: Unlimited time and territory (buyout)

üí∞ Rate: To be discussed

**Who are we looking for?**

‚úÖ Male or Female, approx. 30-40 years old

‚úÖ Fluent spoken English (C1/C2 level) - mandatory requirement

‚úÖ Professional posture and trustworthy appearance (corporate look)

‚úÖ Experience in public speaking and/or on-camera work

‚úÖ Knowledge of cybersecurity topics is a plus

üì© Please send your applications to: casting@pandamotion.pl
Subject line: ‚ÄúCasting ‚Äì LMS training‚Äù

**Please include in your application:**

Name, age, height, city of residence, and phone number

2‚Äì3 current photos (headshot + full body)

Demo/self-tape in English

A recording of a min. 30-second speech in English (any text - read or improvised)

Link to showreel/portfolio (if available)

A brief note about your acting experience

We look forward to receiving your applications! üòä‚ú®

items.text:
Hello everyone! My name is Natali , I'm an aerialist from Argentina with EU passport. I do Swinging Trapeze, Hair Hang and Dance trapeze.

I'm available for short or long contracts since March! 

For more information, showreels and CV, please don't hesitate to contact me!

kind regards

items.text:
**Szukam scenarzysty/scenarzystki dokumentalnej**

**Kogo szukam?**

** ****‚Ä¢**** ****Scenarzysta/ka z do≈õwiadczeniem w dokumentach spo≈Çecznych/≈õledczych (mile widziane tytu≈Çy festiwalowe lub TV/OTT).**

** ****‚Ä¢**** ****Umiejƒôtno≈õƒá pracy na materiale wywiadowym**

** ****‚Ä¢**** ****Warsztat: monta≈º my≈õli, praca z konsultantem merytorycznym.**

** ****‚Ä¢**** ****Atut: znajomo≈õƒá temat√≥w mody/ESG/greenwashing i jƒôzyka social video.**

**Zakres**

** ****‚Ä¢**** ****Script-doctoring + II draft scenariusza na bazie 16 h rozm√≥w + redakcja treatmentu.**

** ****‚Ä¢**** ****Propozycja dramaturgii 3-aktowej (film 80‚Äì90‚Äô) *****lub***** ewentualnie wersji 6√ó30‚Äô serial dokumentalny.**

**Organizacja pracy**

** ****‚Ä¢**** ****Praca zdalna (PL/UE), start: ASAP.**

** ****‚Ä¢**** ****Wsp√≥≈Çpraca p≈Çatna; rozliczenie: rycza≈Çt za etap (umowa o dzie≈Ço/faktura).**

**Czego dotyczy film ? Film o bran≈ºy fashion hybryda dokumentu i narracji pierwszoosobowej (moda, greenwashing, zero waste).**

**Materia≈Ç wyj≈õciowy: 16 godzin nagra≈Ñ rozm√≥w z ekspertami + roboczy treatment.**

**Proszƒô o przes≈Çanie - **Kr√≥tko o sobie + 2‚Äì3 linki do realizacji (lub PDF z opisem projekt√≥w) + dostƒôpno≈õƒá w najbli≈ºszych miesiƒÖcach oraz ramy finansowe.

CASTING FOR SHORT FILM - LEAD & SUPPORTING ROLES
Casting for ‚ÄòI, Me, Merry‚Äô - a 15 minute short film, Family Drama, final year university student project. 

Shooting in Greater Manchester (specific location tbd), Local and nearby talent are encouraged to apply!

Further details for each role can be found in the individual listings/images below, or on backstage (link at the bottom of this post)

CASTING SUMMARY

LEAD

Audrey - Female, playing age 25-30

SUPPORTING

Linda - Female, playing age 40-60

Phil - Male, playing age 40-60

Isobel - Female, playing age 18

Denise - Female, playing age 60-70

Dennis - Male, playing age 60-70

Uncle Tom - Male, playing age 35-50

EXTRAS

All Genders, playing age 35-55

If interested, please contact r.mazurek@edu.salford.ac.uk stating the role in which you are interested, any prior experience, and a head shot. 

OR

Apply through backstage via the link below:

https://www.backstage.com/casting/i-me-merry-3088446/?utm_source=social_share&utm_medium=navigator_share_api&utm_campaign=casting_call

MUST BE AVAILABLE w/c 23RD MARCH UNPAID, FOOD AND TRAVEL REIMBURSED) SHOOTING IN OR AROUND GREATER MANCHESTER EMAIL R.MAZUREK@EDU.SALFORD.AC.UK EK@EDU.SA R.MAZUREK IF INTERESTED'

MUST BE AVAILABLE w/C 23RD MARCH UNPAID, FOOD AND TRAVEL REIMBURSED) SHOOTING IN OR AROUND GREATER MANCHESTER EMAIL R.MAZUREK@EDU.SALFORD.AC.UK R.MAZUREK IF INTERESTED'

MUST BE AVAILABLE w/c 23D MARCH UNPAID, FOOD AND TRAVEL REIMBURSED SHOOTING IN OR AROUND GREATER MANCHESTER EMAIL R.MAZUREK@EDU.SALFORD.AC.UK R.MAZUREK IF INTERESTED'

[CASTING CALL]

Hi Everyone! 

We are currently looking for 2 male actors for a fantastic opportunity to work on short film that will be 3 day shoot between the 16th-22nd March, located in Liverpool. 

Daniel 18-25. A young, naive robber that is forced by

circumstances to steal from a corner shop. 

Baz 30-60. A shop keeper who is a people person but has had experience with robbers before.

This will be unpaid work as it is a uni project, but food and travel fees may be compensated. It is also good to note that this short will be entered into film festivals.

If you or anyone you know is interested in these roles or have any information regarding the film shoot, please feel free to reach out to us at stocktakefilm@gmail.com

FILMING BETWEEN MARCH 16TH-22ND FOR MORE INFORMATION, EMAIL AT STOCKTAKEFLM@GMAIL.COM STOCKTAKEFILM"

sharedPost.text:
‚òÆÔ∏èAUDITION ANNOUNCEMENTS ‚òÆÔ∏è

Come along to our auditions for "A Midsummer Night's Dream" on the 23rd and 25th of February at Phoenix Live, The Harvey Centre, Harlow CM20 1XR

This will be a workshop audition so need to prepare any text. Please come with an idea of what character you would like to have fun with and bring any instruments you wish to use. 

Please note this is a profit share production with show week running from the 31st of May till the 6th of June, with rehearsals on Tuesday and Thursday evenings and Sunday mornings starting from late March. You will be expected to be available for these times and dates. The show and rehearsals will be located in Harlow so only apply if this is doable for you!

To register your interest and let us know you are coming please message us with your preferred date.

We look forward to hearing from you!

- Wayward Theatre Co Harlow

In person LAMDA exams criteria development drama workshop!
Lighthouse SSDC LTD are thrilled to be running their CPD accredited adult LAMDA criteria development workshop on the date below.
Saturday 11th April 2026
11am ‚Äì 3pm LAMDA Criteria Development Workshop Face to Face in London ¬£200
The course will run in South East London and looks at fun games and exercises that help you to teach the criteria and skills needed for students to excel in a LAMDA Acting exam. These can also be useful in other LAMDA subjects. This course is ¬£200 with CPD Accreditation. For the fee, you will receive training from Liz Chambers, an experienced LAMDA Examinations teacher, a teacher training booklet, ongoing support from Lighthouse, and an official CPD certificate. 
To find out more, please contact Liz at hello@lighthousessdc.org or you can book your place here 
https://forms.gle/dxzHQaQa2w1aV6CeA or via our website https://lighthousessdc.org/teacher-training/
We look forward to welcoming you!

üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì SHORT MOCKUMENTARY FILM

We are casting supporting speaking roles for RAPID, a 10-minute mockumentary graduation film produced as part of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

The film will be shot in Bristol from 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026.

This is a student project, unpaid with travel expenses and food provided, intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

STORY:
RAPID follows a small documentary crew as they capture former sprint star Ian Hitchworth‚Äôs attempted comeback through a chaotic athletics trial. Told in a dry, observational mockumentary style, the film blends awkward comedy with uncomfortable realism, allowing humour to emerge through timing, presence, and silence.

ROLES:

SAM ‚Äì Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Sarcastic and cynical. Quietly undermines Ian with dry interrogation and subtle looks to camera.

JOSH ‚Äì Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Sam‚Äôs double act partner. Dry, observant, and enjoys letting awkward pauses land. Aware of the camera.

DUNCAN ‚Äì Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Slow-witted but fascinated by the camera. Blank stares and odd sincerity. Competing more out of boredom than ambition.

These roles rely heavily on timing, subtle reactions, and grounded performances.

KEY INFO:
Location: Bristol
Shoot dates: 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026
Most roles required for one day only (TBC)
Payment: Voluntary (travel expenses & food provided)

TO APPLY:
Please send a headshot and CV (or Spotlight / Mandy link) to:
üì© rapidfilm2026@gmail.com

Ever dreamed of performing at the Edinburgh Fringe?
After our sell-out run in Manchester last October, the brand new, musical comedy, Spraywatch: a Beautiful Rescue, has been selected for the Edinburgh Fringe 2026! 

Audition sign up has begun - if you know any talented humans who could be a good fit for our brand new musical, please get in touch! 

(Please help me out friends by sharing this post!)

MALE ROLES:

ü¶ÄFred - playing age 20‚Äôs/30‚Äôs - local British lifeguard. Eccentric, lovably odd, and paranoid. Prone to using strange, pseudo-Victorian or German-sounding phrasing when excited. Intense crab phobia.

[DUAL ROLE]

ü¶π‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èVictor - playing age 20‚Äôs/30‚Äôs - the British beach boss and secret villain. Charming but secretly manipulative.

üá∫üá∏Twitch - playing age 20‚Äôs/30‚Äôs - the American beach boss. High-energy, "American Dream" intensity with 1990s Hollywood vanity.

Actors must be available for the month of August, plus 2 weeks in July for rehearsal in Manchester. Accommodation in both locations will be covered. 

Any questions, please let me know!

OPEN AUDITIONS ‚Äì BLOOMIN‚Äô CHURCH!

Edinburgh Festival Fringe 2026 + South West Tour

PAID ‚Äì Equity Rates

DROPS ‚Äì Making waves through the arts is casting performers aged 18+ for Bloomin‚Äô Church!, a heartfelt new play heading to the Edinburgh Festival Fringe in summer 2026, followed by a South West tour in October 2026.

HOW TO AUDITION

Auditions will take place across a three-stage process:

Stage 1 ‚Äì Self-Tape Submission

Submit a self-tape audition.

Deadline: Sunday 15th February at 6:00pm

Stage 2 ‚Äì Individual Callbacks

Sherwell United Church (Chapel), Plymouth, PL4 8ER

Friday 27th February

Stage 3 ‚Äì Final Callback (Group Workshop)

Sherwell United Church (Chapel), Plymouth

Saturday 28th February

AUDITION PACK

Full character breakdowns, role requirements, and self-tape instructions can be found here:

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1sbwIgm9kKo5wbnTLrEYqXTmuOFDyGCXm/view?usp=share_link

Strong acting required, with some singing and movement.

Professional and amateur performers welcome.

Inclusive casting

DROPS welcomes performers of all backgrounds, identities, and experiences.

DROPS - making waves through the arts

sharedPost.text:
Vancouver Casting Call

Friends, I am searching for someone to cast in a short, web video I am producing and wanted to widen my net. I am looking for a 50+ aged man from Manitoba with availability here in Vancouver BC (or nearby; Victoria, lower Mainland etc) for a single day between February 23 and 28th. I included some images and a video sample of the variety of folks I am looking for.

The Project: We are producing a short video for distribution on the internet. This isn't a high-pressure sales pitch; it‚Äôs a quiet, grounded reflection.

The Role: "The Manitoba Local"
Age: 50+ something year old male.
EDIT: Yes, this is a paid shoot. If you'd like, send me your preferred day rate as well. 

The Voice: This is the most critical element. We need a voice that is smooth, warm, and resonant. It should feel like a conversation over a morning coffee or a tailgate. No "announcer" voices‚Äîwe want authentic, understated gravitas.

Look: Rustic, rural, blue-collar. We are looking for someone who looks like they‚Äôve put in a hard day‚Äôs work‚Äîweathered skin, honest eyes, and a natural comfort in outdoor settings. Think "The Salt of the Earth." Calm, wise, and connected to Manitoba. We are open to being surprised and have our expectations challenged in the best way possible.

Key Requirements
Ability to deliver a monologue with emotional nuance without being overly dramatic.
A genuine Manitoba/Prairie sensibility is a must.

How to Apply
Please submit the following by email to tristan@vela-creative.com:
-A current headshot or clear photo (no filters, please‚Äîwe want to see the "character" in your face).
-A brief video intro (60 seconds) telling us about your favorite spot in the province. Yes, you can do this on your phone.
-A voice sample or reel if available.

Note: We are prioritizing authenticity. If you‚Äôve spent your life on the land or in a shop and have a voice like velvet, we want to hear from you‚Äîeven if you don't have a traditional acting resume.

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with only cheating. Based on a real story.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

**Free Self-Tape Coaching This Week for Qualified Actors **

**(New Actors Welcome) **

(Normally $65)

If you‚Äôve sent in a pile of Self-Tapes last year and gotten nothing but silence back, that messes with your head. You start replaying your choices. You tweak wardrobe. You second guess the read. You wonder if casting directors even watched past the slate.

Most actors I talk to aren‚Äôt missing talent. They‚Äôre missing clarity.

They‚Äôre ‚Äúacting‚Äù instead of being a real person in a real place having a real experience. And nobody ever slowed down long enough to show them the difference.

That‚Äôs where I come in.

This week, I‚Äôm opening up a limited number of **Free Zoom Coaching and Consultation sessions on your self tapes**.
Normally this is a $65 session.
This week, it‚Äôs free.

We‚Äôll hop on Zoom, go over a script, and I‚Äôll show you exactly what casting directors are responding to and what‚Äôs getting in the way. No fluff. No generic notes. Just clear, practical direction that actually shifts your work.

Work and prepare smarter in 2026 and get results. Feel and BE a real working actor this year.

Spots are limited and once they‚Äôre gone, they‚Äôre gone.

**DM me to grab a spot. Name, How long you‚Äôv been acting, and Where you‚Äôre based.**

***Serious actors only.**

***Must be 18 yrs old.**

items.text:
UCCS DIGITAL FILMMAKING CAPSTONE FILM AUDITIONS

Our UCCS capstone film production students are gearing up to shoot their capstone short films, and this year there will be a whopping 18 films to audition for! Auditions begin this Saturday, February 14 and continue through March 1. I try to structure the auditions and the film shoots in a way that is as actor-friendly as possible:
* Auditions are held on UCCS campus on the weekends when there is free parking
* I have students hold auditions in groups of 3, so you can potentially audition for up to 3 films in one visit (you will be asked in the Calendly signup to note all of the films and roles you would like to audition for)
* Each film is only allowed one 12-hour shoot day between March 7 - May 3, so you can potentially act in multiple films with a minimal time commitment
* All filming locations must be in or very near to Colorado Springs

COPY OF FINAL FILM AND FOOTAGE

Students are required to use their OneDrive accounts to share a copy of the finished film AND all film footage with actors by the end of the semester (I enforce this by withholding the grade on their film if they don‚Äôt provide proof that they‚Äôve shared everything with their actors). This is a great way to get footage for your reel.

HOW TO SIGN UP FOR AUDITIONS

The following link will take you to a OneDrive folder with six audition date folders. Within each folder are the three casting calls for that date, and all three films use the same Calendly signup link (so if you are having trouble copying and pasting link from one casting call, check the other casting calls in the same folder for the link).

Casting Calls for all 18 films:

[[https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)

* The production date and audition date is listed on each casting call, as are character breakdowns. Please make sure you are available on the production date and fit the requirements of the role you are auditioning for before signing up for a time. items.summary:
UCCS DIGITAL FILMMAKING CAPSTONE FILM AUDITIONS

Our UCCS capstone film production students are gearing up to shoot their capstone short films, and this year there will be a whopping 18 films to audition for! Auditions begin this Saturday, February 14 and continue through March 1. I try to structure the auditions and the film shoots in a way that is as actor-friendly as possible:
* Auditions are held on UCCS campus on the weekends when there is free parking
* I have students hold auditions in groups of 3, so you can potentially audition for up to 3 films in one visit (you will be asked in the Calendly signup to note all of the films and roles you would like to audition for)
* Each film is only allowed one 12-hour shoot day between March 7 - May 3, so you can potentially act in multiple films with a minimal time commitment
* All filming locations must be in or very near to Colorado Springs

COPY OF FINAL FILM AND FOOTAGE

Students are required to use their OneDrive accounts to share a copy of the finished film AND all film footage with actors by the end of the semester (I enforce this by withholding the grade on their film if they don‚Äôt provide proof that they‚Äôve shared everything with their actors). This is a great way to get footage for your reel.

HOW TO SIGN UP FOR AUDITIONS

The following link will take you to a OneDrive folder with six audition date folders. Within each folder are the three casting calls for that date, and all three films use the same Calendly signup link (so if you are having trouble copying and pasting link from one casting call, check the other casting calls in the same folder for the link).

Casting Calls for all 18 films:

[[https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)](https://uccsoffice365-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jhubert3_uccs_edu/IgBumsW98S11Qb_DBiWAEsW3AbBET7sreizbAs1T-my-Pzc?e=9ATsUm)

* The production date and audition date is listed on each casting call, as are character breakdowns. Please make sure you are available on the production date and fit the requirements of the role you are auditioning for before signing up for a time. If you have questions about individual films (including whether or not they will accept virtual auditions), please reach out to the contact email on the casting call. If you are having trouble accessing the casting calls, please DM me and I‚Äôll get back to you ASAP.

üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì SHORT MOCKUMENTARY FILM

We are casting supporting speaking roles for RAPID, a 10-minute mockumentary graduation film produced as part of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

The film will be shot in Bristol from 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026.

This is a student project, unpaid with travel expenses and food provided, intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

STORY:
RAPID follows a small documentary crew as they capture former sprint star Ian Hitchworth‚Äôs attempted comeback through a chaotic athletics trial. Told in a dry, observational mockumentary style, the film blends awkward comedy with uncomfortable realism, allowing humour to emerge through timing, presence, and silence.

ROLES:

SAM ‚Äì Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Sarcastic and cynical. Quietly undermines Ian with dry interrogation and subtle looks to camera.

JOSH ‚Äì Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Sam‚Äôs double act partner. Dry, observant, and enjoys letting awkward pauses land. Aware of the camera.

DUNCAN ‚Äì Changing Room Athlete
Male, 20s
Slow-witted but fascinated by the camera. Blank stares and odd sincerity. Competing more out of boredom than ambition.

These roles rely heavily on timing, subtle reactions, and grounded performances.

KEY INFO:
Location: Bristol
Shoot dates: 2nd‚Äì6th March 2026
Most roles required for one day only (TBC)
Payment: Voluntary (travel expenses & food provided)

TO APPLY:
Please send a headshot and CV (or Spotlight / Mandy link) to:
üì© rapidfilm2026@gmail.com

items.text:
TONIGHT at The Two Brewers (Clapham) I‚Äôm beyond proud to welcome Martin Sherman on stage for The Show People Podcast LIVE.

Martin is one of the most important voices in queer theatre. His landmark play BENT opened at the Royal Court, transferred to the West End starring Ian McKellen, went on to Broadway (Richard Gere), and was later adapted for film. It‚Äôs a piece of writing that helped shape how queer lives are seen on stage.

His work spans decades across theatre and film, including ROSE (National Theatre/Broadway) and the BAFTA-nominated screenplay MRS HENDERSON PRESENTS, plus a body of writing that‚Äôs been produced in more than 60 countries.

Across theatre and film, Martin has been nominated for two Tony Awards, two Olivier Awards and two BAFTA Awards, and this evening is a chance to hear directly from a writer whose work has shaped queer storytelling for generations.

üéüÔ∏è Tickets are strictly limited to 100

+++ Faire Gagen Kundgebung am Brandenburger Tor sorgte f√ºr √ºberraschendes Medien-Interesse +++

Mediendienst laut-werden.de  wurde trotz unserer sehr kurzfristigen Demo-Anmeldung auf uns aufmerksam und drehte ein Statement von Faire Gagen auf dem Pariser Platz.

Erkl√§rung:
Wegen extremer  Wetterlage

üéôÔ∏è From Corrie‚Ä¶ to Ted Lasso.
In the latest episode of the Sound & Scope Podcast, we sit down with acclaimed actor Bill Fellows for an honest, funny and surprisingly revealing conversation about a career built on graft, luck and great scripts.

From growing up in Middlesbrough‚Ä¶

To starring in Coronation Street‚Ä¶

To performing in Blood Brothers‚Ä¶

To appearing in Lady Macbeth‚Ä¶

To nearly not sending the self-tape that landed him a role in the global hit Ted Lasso‚Ä¶

This is the real story behind the roles.

We talk about:

üé≠ The drama school audition that changed everything

üé¨ Why great scripts matter more than fame

üì∫ The pressure of long-running dramas like Corrie

‚öΩ The Ted Lasso audition he almost didn‚Äôt do

üéüÔ∏è Working class roots, theatre, TV and staying grounded

This episode is co-produced with Tees Valley International Film Festival, recorded live during the festival weekend.

If you care about acting, filmmaking, British TV, or the reality behind the industry,  this one‚Äôs for you.

üéß Watch here:

üëâ https://youtu.be/U1cdwpRPvN8

For more info on Tees Valley International Film Festival visit:

üëâ https://www.tviff.co.uk

Submissions are now open for TVIFF 2026:

‚ÄúThe greatest celebration of creative media the world has ever known!‚Äù

üëâ https://filmfreeway.com/TeesValleyInternationalFilmFestival

items.title: Background Call

items.text:
CASTING CALL

Project: indie film

Plot:

A woman in her 20s drifts through friendships, impulses, and quiet disappointments, unsure of who she is or how to move forward. As her world begins to fracture, she is forced to confront her own patterns of blame, desire, and avoidance. Through solitude and fleeting human connections, she slowly learns to sit with sadness, not as something to escape, but as a guide toward self-understanding and the courage to begin again.

 

Shooting dates: Mid-End of March 2026 (mostly weekends)

Shooting location: Vancouver and the greater area

 

Please submit your resume, headshot(s), and demo reel or self-tape by email: [theprivilegeofsorrow@gmail.com](mailto:theprivilegeofsorrow@gmail.com)

 

Volunteer Position

 

PARTY FRIEND #1

Male, 20s

Cocky, confrontational party goer. Loves night thrills; beach partying, running, shouting, high energy after a wild house party.

 

PARTY FRIEND #2

Male/female/non-binary, 20s

Easygoing follower, impulsive and playful. Down for anything; night beach run, laughing, hyping the group, physical, carefree energy.

 

PARTY FRIEND #3

Male/female/non-binary, 20s

At a chaotic party, they notice a girl passed out. Later, in a quieter moment, they end up talking while the party continues.

 

GLASSES

Male, 20s
Tall, robust, dominant presence. Confident, physical, impulsive; intense hookup energy in a crowded party setting.

 

GYM EMPLOYEE

Neutral, mildly defensive, trained to de-escalate. Repeats policy language automatically, avoids eye contact, prioritizes rules over empathy.

 

GAS STATION WORKER

Irritable, territorial, quick to escalate. Defensive authority figure; confrontational energy in a late-night, mundane conflict over a vending machine.

 

We are also casting background performers for the party scenes. Please indicate your interest when submitting.

items.text:
POWERHOUSE CASTING is looking for real people (Ages 18+) to participate in a paid conversation project.  

Seeking Real People Having Real Conversations.

Get Paid to Chat With a Friend ‚Äì Each Individual will be paid $35 USD per Hour 
 
We‚Äôre partnering with a technology research company that is studying how people naturally speak, react, and interact in everyday conversation. The goal is to help improve how future digital tools understand real human communication.
 
What‚Äôs involved?
‚Ä¢ A one-hour+ Zoom conversation with a friend
‚Ä¢ Casual, unscripted, natural discussion
‚Ä¢ You can participate for up to 5 hours total
‚Ä¢ Paid $35 USD per hour per person ($48 CAD).  
*Direct payment to you as long as you follow the criterion.
That means you and your friend could each earn up to $175 USD (All Inclusive) for simply having real conversations.
 
Who we‚Äôre looking for:
‚Ä¢ Friends who are comfortable on camera
‚Ä¢ All ages 18+
‚Ä¢ All backgrounds, and lived experiences welcome
‚Ä¢ Natural, expressive communicators

No acting is required. No memorizing lines. Just real people being themselves having a conversation.
This is a straightforward, paid research opportunity conducted remotely from home.
 
VERY IMPORTANT NOTES TO KEEP IN MIND BEFORE RECORDING. MAKE SURE YOU DO THE FOLLOWING IN ORDER FOR YOUR FOOTAGE TO BE CONSIDERED 
 
EVERYONE MUST BE 18 YEARS OLD OR OLDER 
 
YOU MUST RECORD IN 1080p RESOLUTION OR HIGHER 
 
YOU MUST RECORD YOUR FOOTAGE USING A LAPTOP OR COMPUTER. DO NOT USE YOUR PHONE
 
DO NOT WEAR ANY FACIAL ACCESSORIES WHEN RECORDING (NO HATS, NO GLASSES ETC.)
 
YOU MUST HAVE MINIMAL OR NO FACIAL HAIR TO BE CONSIDERED. 
THEY NEED TO SEE YOUR UNOBSTRUCTED FACE AS CLEARLY AS POSSIBLE  
 
 
If you‚Äôre interested, please follow this link for more instructions 
 
LINK: 
https://velvet.video
Click "sign up". Once prompted for a code, use GXLO-86IL-ZTQ0

‚Ä¢ All backgrounds, and lived experiences welcome
‚Ä¢ Natural, expressive communicators

No acting is required. No memorizing lines. Just real people being themselves having a conversation.
This is a straightforward, paid research opportunity conducted remotely from home.
 
VERY IMPORTANT NOTES TO KEEP IN MIND BEFORE RECORDING. MAKE SURE YOU DO THE FOLLOWING IN ORDER FOR YOUR FOOTAGE TO BE CONSIDERED 
 
EVERYONE MUST BE 18 YEARS OLD OR OLDER 
 
YOU MUST RECORD IN 1080p RESOLUTION OR HIGHER

YOU MUST HAVE MINIMAL OR NO FACIAL HAIR TO BE CONSIDERED.

items.text:
Looking to cast a lead role in our student film
please email r.khosssa-kulair23@lipa.ac.uk or DM betterman.lipa on instagram for more information ! 

HARRISON ‚Äî Supporting Lead (Male)

Playing Age: 22‚Äì30ÔøΩAccent: Neutral British (flexible)ÔøΩRole Type: Charismatic / Psychological / Romantic-ThrillerÔøΩScreen Time: High Supporting (appears throughout film)

Character Summary:ÔøΩHarrison is magnetic, calm and intensely perceptive ‚Äî the kind of person who seems to understand you before you speak. He appears in Emma‚Äôs life at her lowest moment and becomes her emotional anchor‚Ä¶ or possibly something far more dangerous. His kindness feels genuine, but always carries an unsettling edge. The audience should never be entirely sure whether he is protector, manipulator, or both.

He rarely raises his voice. Instead, his power comes from stillness, eye contact and emotional precision. His presence shifts a room ‚Äî comforting one moment, quietly threatening the next.

Performance Style:ÔøΩNaturalistic and restrained. The actor must communicate subtext and tension through micro-expressions, pauses and controlled body language rather than overt emotion.

Key Traits:

* Quiet confidence

* Observant and emotionally intelligent

* Gentle but subtly possessive

* Romantic with unsettling undertones

* Ambiguous morality

Character Arc:ÔøΩBegins as a mysterious stranger offering comfort, gradually embedding himself into Emma‚Äôs life. As events escalate, his protectiveness becomes increasingly intense, blurring the line between care and control. 

Script Better Man

Actor Notes:ÔøΩLooking for an actor comfortable playing duality ‚Äî warm and safe on the surface, but capable of conveying underlying danger without melodrama. Think: intimate psychological tension rather than overt villainy.

Comparable Tone (not impersonation):ÔøΩJoe Goldberg (You), Tom Ripley, early Patrick Bateman charm without the camp

items.text:
Hey folks, so here‚Äôs my little pitch, I suppose! I‚Äôd introduce myself, but the profile is right there;

Actually, scratch that, it feels weird starting without at least my first name. I‚Äôm Will! I‚Äôve been a lifelong creative, attending several drama schools in my twenties and continuously writing scripts that I‚Äôve often abandoned halfway through.

However, no longer! I set myself a goal this year of writing 6 short films, each with a different theme and genre, in an anthology style akin to Inside No. 9 or Black Mirror.

As a result, I‚Äôm very pleased to showcase the first finished screenplay with a short synopsis here and potentially cast the project as follows;

DISCLAIMER:

**THIS PROJECT CONTAINS VERY STRONG & MATURE THEMES NOT LIMITED TO BUT INCLUDING SEXUAL REFERENCES, PROFANITY & SELF-HARM. PLEASE ONLY APPLY IF YOU ARE 18+ AND ARE NOT SENSITIVE TO THIS MATERIAL. **
**(UNPAID OPPORTUNITY)**

**LOCATIONS: NORTH LIVERPOOL AREA.**

Synopsis:

A lonely thirty-something following a bad breakup stumbles across a group of paranormal investigators who have a very different take on what life after death could truly be, and what happens to an unfortunate few.

Casting Call:

**Director/Camera Operator: **I plan to film this project myself if necessary. Although I lack professional equipment, there will be scenes better handled by someone with more expertise in this area.

**Tex (20-30s Female):** Edgy and sarcastic with a sharp wit, charisma comes naturally to her with a goth/emo aesthetic.

**Scoob (20-30s Male): **A straight-talking rebel to the system, rocker/gothic aesthetic similar to Tex. Heavy smoker on the path to degeneracy.

**Pol (20-30s Female): **Academically astute yet magnetized toward those who follow unconventional paths, supportive and generally well-meaning.

**Rhys (20+ Male): **Through and through an objectivist, studying and research are his bread and butter. The archivist and quiet guide of the group, with an intellectually introverted disposition.

üìç Atlanta, GA

üíµ Paid Principal Day Rate | Non-Union | Independent Production

Production is casting two (2) East Asian male actors for a gritty, character-driven pilot set inside a correctional facility. 

These are performance-forward roles requiring strong physical presence, emotional control, and compelling nonverbal acting.

**CHEN (22‚Äì32)**

Male, East Asian, lean build

Older brother

Controlled, observant, strategic

Minimal dialogue

Must convey internal power and authority through stillness

Portrays an incarcerated individual

**JIN (20‚Äì30)**

Male, East Asian, lean/athletic build

Younger brother

Intense yet disciplined

Strong physical performer

Comfortable with choreographed fight sequences

Portrays an incarcerated individual

* Physical performance with choreographed fight sequences (no high-risk stunts)
* Martial arts or movement training a plus
* Mandarin or Cantonese ability a plus (brief dialogue)
* Must be comfortable portraying incarcerated characters
* Atlanta local hire only

items.text:
UCCS Digital Filmmaking Capstone Film Casting Call

Hello! I am looking for actors to audition for my UCCS Capstone Student Short Film. Details below:

Title: Unforced Errors

Genre: Drama

Logline: Matt is convinced his recently deceased father loved his brother more than him, but his brother Josh unknowingly feels the same way. As Matt searches for his dad‚Äôs old baseball card collection, the brothers soon discover that their father‚Äôs love was unconditional.

Roles: 

**Matt (20 ‚Äì 26 years old) - Male, Any Ethnicity:**

Matt is a true younger brother. He is always trying his best to impress everyone around him and make himself noticed, but he never feels like he is good enough. He loves his brother Josh, but he has always been jealous of his relationship with their father.

 

**Josh (22 ‚Äì 28 years old) - Male, Any Ethnicity:**

Josh was a high school baseball athlete, but not the jock/bully type. He has a strong exterior demeanor that hides how he truly feels: like he was never good enough for his professional baseball-playing father. While he would never want to admit it, he is jealous of his younger brother Matt and the relationship he had with their father.

Director: Zion Wilson

Producer: Onyx Riccelli

Production Type: Student Film

UCCS Digital Filmmaking Capstone Film Casting Call

Hello! I am looking for actors to audition for my UCCS Capstone Student Short Film. Details below:

Title: Unforced Errors

Genre: Drama

Logline: Matt is convinced his recently deceased father loved his brother more than him, but his brother Josh unknowingly feels the same way. As Matt searches for his dad‚Äôs old baseball card collection, the brothers soon discover that their father‚Äôs love was unconditional.

Roles: 

**Matt (20 ‚Äì 26 years old) - Male, Any Ethnicity:**

Matt is a true younger brother. He is always trying his best to impress everyone around him and make himself noticed, but he never feels like he is good enough. He loves his brother Josh, but he has always been jealous of his relationship with their father.

 

**Josh (22 ‚Äì 28 years old) - Male, Any Ethnicity:**

Josh was a high school baseball athlete, but not the jock/bully type. He has a strong exterior demeanor that hides how he truly feels: like he was never good enough for his professional baseball-playing father. While he would never want to admit it, he is jealous of his younger brother Matt and the relationship he had with their father.

Director: Zion Wilson

Producer: Onyx Riccelli

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: unforcederrorsfilm@gmail.com

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Non-Paid

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Date: Saturday, February 14th, 11am-7pm. 

Audition Location:** **UCCS Campus: El Pomar Center 103 (directions are included in the appointment confirmation).

Auditions are by appointment only. Please use the link included in the attached casting call to sign up for a time slot.

Shooting Schedule: Saturday, March 7th. Please be available for the entire day.

Project Description: UCCS Capstone Student Short Film

Please email us at unforcederrorsfilm@gmail.com if you have any questions. Thank you!

CASTING CALL - ASAP

13/02/25

The Party No One Wanted (Short Film)

**A dark comedy about grief and family relationships.**

Robbie and Mary have to get through an excruciating memorial that has a DJ, karaoke and a pregnancy announcement / gender reveal planned by their half sister Lisa.

Please fill in this form if interested: [https://forms.gle/4N4tdaMwFQ6aBnga7](https://forms.gle/4N4tdaMwFQ6aBnga7) 

* **Shooting 6th - 9th March in TW19**
* Auditions in Elephant and Castle within the next few weeks
* **Travel Expenses Paid**
* There are also multiple smaller roles and extras needed please see the form for more information
* Student film hoping to go to Film festivals
* **Steve** (57-70yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Mary, Robbie and Lisa‚Äôs dad doesn‚Äôt get involved in the arguing he‚Äôs still devastated by the loss of his wife but insists he‚Äôs fine.
* **Lisa** (39-47yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Self centred and definitely doesn‚Äôt know whats appropriate at a memorial. 
* **Natalie** (49-65yrs)
   * A close family friend who has taken on a bit of a motherly role to everyone, kind and soft spoken.
* **Bill** (50-65yrs) 
   * The drunk best friend of steve who has awful timing for his awkward comments. Very funny character

**Character Bios: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing)** **

OPEN AUDITION for Julius Caesar by secret actors in secret spaces. Reviewed as 'Shakespeare that is thrillingly new and thrums with raw energy' by British Theatre Guide. The promenade performance puts the audience face to face with the acting as actors in the audience and throughout Reading Abbey Ruins reveal themselves as actors during the show.

WHERE: Rehearsal in central London and Reading. Performance in Reading.
WHEN: Saturday 30th May to Saturday 20th June (rest days on Tuesday 2nd June, 9th June and 16th June). Evening performances in the week. Evening and matinee performances on weekends.
REMUNERATION: ¬£12.71 per hour (National Living Wage) for 100 hours of rehearsal and performance (inclusive of holiday pay).
ELIGIBILITY: Open audition for actors 18 years and older. Please contact us if you need any reasonable adjustments to audition.
AUDITION: Please submit a self tape of a monologue or soliloquy from any of Shakespeare's plays.
DEADLINE: Saturday 28th February at 11:59pm
EMAIL: shakespeareunstaged@gmail.com
CALLBACK: Saturday 28th March in central London

#juliuscaesar #shakespeare #secretshakespeare Secret Shakespeare #auditions #actors #acting #auditioning #readingabbeyruins Reading Abbey Quarter

sharedPost.text:
Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with only cheating. Based on a real story.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.
